<t>CREATE TABLE movies (movie_id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR, genre VARCHAR, release_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE actors (actor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE, gender VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE directors (director_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE);

CREATE TABLE movie_cast (movie_id INT, actor_id INT, character_name VARCHAR, PRIMARY KEY (movie_id, actor_id));</t><s>SELECT * FROM movies;</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE movies (movie_id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR, genre VARCHAR, release_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE actors (actor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE, gender VARCHAR);</t><s>select title, genre, first_name, last_name, character_name from movies inner join movie_cast on movies.movie_id = movie_cast.movie_id inner join actors on actors.actor_id = movie_cast.actor_id;</s>

CREATE TABLE directors (director_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE);</t><s>select title, genre, first_name, last_name, character_name from movies inner join movie_cast on movies.movie_id = movie_cast.movie_id inner join actors on actors.actor_id = movie_cast.actor_id inner join directors on directors.director_id = movies.director_id;</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE movies (movie_id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR, genre VARCHAR, release_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE actors (actor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE, gender VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE directors (director_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE);

CREATE TABLE movie_cast (movie_id INT, actor_id INT, character_name VARCHAR, PRIMARY KEY (movie_id, actor_id));</t><s>SELECT title, genre, first_name, last_name, character_name FROM movies INNER JOIN movie_cast ON movies.movie_id = movie_cast.movie_id INNER JOIN actors ON actors.actor_id = movie_cast.actor_id INNER JOIN directors ON directors.director_id = movies.director_id INNER JOIN actors ON directors.director_id = directors.actor_id WHERE title LIKE '%Action%';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE movies (movie_id INT PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR, genre VARCHAR, release_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE actors (actor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE, gender VARCHAR);

CREATE TABLE directors (director_id INT PRIMARY KEY, first_name VARCHAR, last_name VARCHAR, dob DATE);

CREATE TABLE movie_cast (movie_id INT, actor_id INT, character_name VARCHAR, PRIMARY KEY (movie_id, actor_id));</t><s>select title, genre, first_name, last_name, character_name from movies inner join movie_cast on movies.movie_id = movie_cast.movie_id inner join actors on actors.actor_id = movie_cast.actor_id inner join directors on directors.director_id = movies.director_id inner join actors on directors.director_id = directors.actor_id where title like '%action%';</s>

CREATE TABLE studios (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, headquarters VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE movies (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, genre VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, release_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE actors (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, age INT NOT NULL, gender VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE directors (id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL, age INT NOT NULL, gender VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL, nationality VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);</t><s>select name, age, gender from actors where gender = 'female';</s>
